<title>UK: Lehman appoints new head of fixed income sales.</title>
<headline>Lehman appoints new head of fixed income sales.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Lehman Brothers said in a statement on Tuesday it had appointed Gordon Mori as executive director in fixed income sales.</p>
<p>Mori will be head of the group responsible for sales coverage of Japanese and Asian institutions in Europe.</p>
<p>Mori will report to John McDonald, managing director and head of fixed income sales for Europe.</p>
<p>Mori joins Lehman from Merrill Lynch where he spent six and a half years covering Japanese institutions in Europe for fixed income products.</p>
